Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.08,0:00:04.66,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ladies and gentlemen,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.92,0:00:07.93,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I bring you marvelous illusions that \Nmake this town sparkle at night!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.22,0:00:12.49,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I hope you enjoy the miracle of seeing \Nthe true face of a hated villain.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.47,0:00:18.81,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Find him!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.81,0:00:22.46,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Kid the Phantom Thief has to be \Nhiding somewhere around here!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.21,0:00:29.21,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}This is finally the night I'm gonna \Nslap iron bracelets on those wrists!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.26,0:00:30.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This isn't good...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.05,0:00:35.51,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The forecast called for rain, but I didn't \Nknow it'd be too heavy for my hang glider!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.26,0:00:39.26,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It sounds like you're in a spot \Nof trouble, Phantom Thief.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.64,0:00:43.55,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,U-Um... And who might you be?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.55,0:00:44.83,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Me?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.27,0:00:47.68,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,My name is Nightmare.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.00,0:00:52.03,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm on your side.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.96,0:02:37.26,Signs - Thief Title,,0000,0000,0000,,Dark Knight
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.56,0:02:37.26,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Nightmare?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.38,0:02:41.26,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You're saying he helped Kid escape,\N Superintendent Chaki?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.26,0:02:42.81,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.81,0:02:47.27,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The Second Investigation Division \Njust got a mail about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.58,0:02:51.72,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It said, "This time, I'm meeting \NKid the Phantom Thief as a friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.72,0:02:55.27,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,On next Friday night, the 13th, at 8:00,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.56,0:03:01.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,the two of us will show you a \Nnightmare at the Shuho Art Museum."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.53,0:03:04.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Who is this "Nightmare"?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.58,0:03:07.84,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,A weird guy who wears a mask.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.84,0:03:11.01,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But he partners up with thieves \Nfrom all over the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.01,0:03:17.49,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He's a mysterious mastermind who takes half \Nof the loot as his reward for coming up with
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.49,0:03:19.22,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,the perfect methods and escape route.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.22,0:03:21.47,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Why would Kid team up with him?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.11,0:03:27.30,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The good news is that any thief who \Ncooperates with him is invariably caught by
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.30,0:03:29.98,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,the local police before dawn,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.98,0:03:34.35,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,and some have even been \Nshot trying to escape.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.35,0:03:37.48,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Still clutching their half of the spoils...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.52,0:03:43.74,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,So there's a rumor going \Naround among thieves.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.18,0:03:49.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyone who works with Nightmare and \Nsafely makes it through the night
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.60,0:03:56.25,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,will be able to shake off any nightmares of \Nthis world and attain endless good fortune.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.01,0:04:02.62,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure Kid the Phantom Thief is \Nblinded by the promise of good fortune.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.62,0:04:05.63,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This way, you'll finally be \Nset free from Kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.26,0:04:08.12,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.12,0:04:13.27,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Thieves who are singled out by Nightmare \Neither end up caught or dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.64,0:04:16.40,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Although, as a representative \Nof Japanese law enforcement,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.40,0:04:20.30,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I hope to catch both of them alive \Nby any means possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.30,0:04:22.03,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Japanese...?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.50,0:04:27.53,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Nightmare is an international criminal \Nwho wreaks havoc all over the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.53,0:04:31.09,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Naturally, agents will be \Ncoming here with a Red Notice.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.09,0:04:33.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Red Notice?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.20,0:04:38.42,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,An international arrest warrant seeking \Ncustody of a fugitive criminal,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.42,0:04:40.70,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,demanding we turn him over.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.70,0:04:41.80,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You didn't know that?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.80,0:04:44.80,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Then don't tell me these agents \Nthat are coming over...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.80,0:04:48.33,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. The international police organization.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.33,0:04:50.31,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Interpol.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.06,0:04:55.63,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,136 officers in front! 103 officers in back!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.63,0:04:59.57,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,185 officers in the main building! \N47 officers on the roof!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.57,0:05:02.23,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Six helicopters! Everyone is in place!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.23,0:05:05.69,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,All right! Stand by in position\N until it's time!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.69,0:05:07.74,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Keep your eyes open!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.74,0:05:09.49,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.49,0:05:11.66,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Glad you could make it, Interpol!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.66,0:05:14.25,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Nakamori, the guy who's \Ngot this place locked down!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.25,0:05:16.03,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh... Kaito-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.54,0:05:19.46,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Right. You called me here...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.46,0:05:24.62,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, right. I wanted you take a look \Nat my security system here later on.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.62,0:05:26.76,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Like Kid, you're good with tricks.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.14,0:05:30.40,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Check it out with an illusionist's eyes,\N then give me your opinion.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.40,0:05:31.51,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.51,0:05:32.77,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,See you later, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.77,0:05:34.69,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm counting on you!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.33,0:05:39.76,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, that suits me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.76,0:05:44.65,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Since he's willing to show Kid how his \Ntricks are done before the show starts.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.65,0:05:48.66,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And what do you find so amusing, \NKid the Phantom Thief?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.17,0:05:51.68,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Just kidding!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.68,0:05:53.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,A-Aoko?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.20,0:05:55.34,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What's with that uniform?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.34,0:05:57.00,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I told a member of the riot squad
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.00,0:06:00.81,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,that I wanted to try on the uniform \Nsometime, and he lent me a spare!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.81,0:06:02.67,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell my dad, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.05,0:06:05.66,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I actually wanted to show him, too...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.66,0:06:06.63,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Him?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.63,0:06:07.17,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.50,0:06:09.68,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you gonna fight the bad guy, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.03,0:06:13.18,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.85,0:06:16.42,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll capture him, then \Npound some sense into him.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.42,0:06:19.36,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Because evil musn't be\N allowed to prosper!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.36,0:06:21.69,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Then you're on the same side \Nas Papa! Good luck!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.03,0:06:24.44,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,"Papa"? Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.74,0:06:28.95,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Kenta Connery.\N Papa is Chuck Connery.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.24,0:06:33.00,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He's been on the trail of that bad guy,\N Nightmare, for the longest time!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.00,0:06:36.58,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He's got an important job with Interpol!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.76,0:06:39.58,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I apologize for arriving late.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.58,0:06:44.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the additional material on Nightmare \NI was telling you about on the phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.20,0:06:47.41,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,B-But I didn't think you'd be coming alone...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.41,0:06:50.70,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I have people standing by outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.70,0:06:53.94,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We're just here to cooperate \Nwith you, the local police.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.94,0:06:55.81,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We don't have the right to make an arrest.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.52,0:06:59.23,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,At any rate, you speak Japanese very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.23,0:07:01.87,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,My wife is Japanese.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.87,0:07:03.65,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Although she passed away three years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.65,0:07:04.73,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Papa!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.48,0:07:08.10,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,K-Kenta!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.74,0:07:10.90,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Shoot! Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.89,0:07:13.29,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.29,0:07:17.24,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I slipped out of the home since I knew\N you were coming back to Japan!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.24,0:07:18.66,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,"Home"?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.66,0:07:22.00,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ever since my wife passed, I've had \Nan orphanage take care of him.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.37,0:07:27.00,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I travel all over the world for work,\N so I can't raise him properly.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.34,0:07:33.25,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Kenta, you "slipped out"? \NI'm sure they're worried about you!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.25,0:07:36.60,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's fine! I said I was gonna \Nstay with you at your hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.60,0:07:39.07,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But I don't know what to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.07,0:07:41.97,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't have time to drop him \Noff at the home.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.76,0:07:43.60,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I have to go back?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.08,0:07:46.36,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Then shall I take him back?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.36,0:07:47.57,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,She's a quick-change artist now?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.57,0:07:48.92,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Um, who is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.92,0:07:50.66,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,My daughter, Aoko!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.66,0:07:53.56,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,She sometimes brings me dinner \Nwhen I'm on the job.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.56,0:07:55.82,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Then please take care of my son.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.37,0:07:57.82,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.33,0:08:00.79,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And I'm leaving Nightmare in your hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.79,0:08:04.32,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay. I'll arrest him, along with Kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.32,0:08:09.17,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We've both been carrying heavy baggage for \Nyears, so it'll be nice to finally set it down.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.17,0:08:10.51,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It will.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.51,0:08:11.59,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, then...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.56,0:08:16.52,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,One question. Frankly speaking, \Nwhat's Nightmare like?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.52,0:08:17.96,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's a good question.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.96,0:08:21.52,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If we're to believe the words \Nof all his arrested partners,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.52,0:08:27.01,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Nightmare is a cunning demon \Nwho gets into a person's mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.49,0:08:29.53,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,sees through everything, \Nand manipulates them.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.53,0:08:31.80,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.80,0:08:35.17,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,A demon who manipulates people's minds...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.17,0:08:37.60,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That may be true.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.04,0:08:42.46,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think, Kid the Phantom Thief?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.46,0:08:45.12,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,How is the escape route I selected for you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.12,0:08:47.79,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Worthy of your reputation, Nightmare.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.18,0:08:51.79,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, if you know my name already, \Nthat saves us some time.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.79,0:08:53.77,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Next Friday the 13th...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.77,0:08:56.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, but I'm not teaming up with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.05,0:08:58.83,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? So this is how you're going to play it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.83,0:09:01.81,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The rumors were right. You're a lone wolf.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.17,0:09:05.70,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Or actually, you have one associate.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.70,0:09:09.64,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,A loyal old man who sometimes \Nimpersonates you and helps you escape.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.64,0:09:10.57,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.62,0:09:13.32,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe now you understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.70,0:09:16.16,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing can escape me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.16,0:09:19.16,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You are under my constant surveillance.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.46,0:09:24.43,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. Even now.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.83,0:09:27.21,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Nightmare!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.21,0:09:29.46,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,So what's the prey?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.71,0:09:35.02,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Nightmare and Kid are after \Nthese earrings, which have
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.02,0:09:37.50,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,black opals embedded in them.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.50,0:09:38.72,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Dark Knight!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.72,0:09:43.22,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And the jewel is contained in \Nwhat I developed to stymie Kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.22,0:09:45.22,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,My security system!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.22,0:09:48.66,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,To open the lid of that hard glass case,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.66,0:09:52.81,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,you'd have to remove \Nthese electrified chains.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.81,0:09:55.99,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's simple yet impregnable, don't you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.99,0:09:57.64,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.64,0:09:59.80,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And what's the liquid in the case?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.80,0:10:03.49,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Water! Black opals' weakness is dryness.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.03,0:10:05.90,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Right, Director Kondo?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.90,0:10:11.00,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, the director said he can't fight on an \Nempty stomach, so he ducked out for dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.00,0:10:15.79,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The outside length and height are 48 cm.\N The diameter inside is 16 cm.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.79,0:10:18.67,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,So what do you think of \Nthis system, Kaito-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.14,0:10:21.01,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I don't think it can be stolen.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.01,0:10:23.01,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You'd have to open the lid.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.01,0:10:24.26,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.56,0:10:26.52,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Aoko? You're still here?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.52,0:10:31.27,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, he insists on "taking down\N the bad guy with Papa."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.63,0:10:35.15,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, let's leave this \Nto your papa and my dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.15,0:10:39.17,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Forget it! I'm gonna fight, too!\N I'm gonna be like Papa!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.41,0:10:41.94,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, what's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.94,0:10:43.16,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.16,0:10:45.96,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I-I'm fine. I have my medicine.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.41,0:10:48.91,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's a painkiller!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.15,0:10:55.00,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The doctor said I have a \Nbad guy living in my head
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.00,0:10:57.32,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,and I need to have surgery...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.32,0:10:58.92,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Surgery?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.92,0:11:00.68,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But it's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.68,0:11:02.03,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Papa said!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.03,0:11:07.43,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If Nightmare goes away, then he'll be able to \Ndrive off the evil, wild horse in my head!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.84,0:11:11.63,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Then we'll be able to live \Ntogether forever, he said!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.44,0:11:15.69,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, are you hungry?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.13,0:11:19.37,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Then why don't we get curry and rice\N at a family restaurant?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.37,0:11:23.23,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If you eat some carrots, \Nmaybe the bad horse will quiet down.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.23,0:11:24.45,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,O-Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.78,0:11:27.42,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Speaking of horses, did you see him in there?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.42,0:11:28.84,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Who do you keep talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.84,0:11:30.56,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's strange...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.56,0:11:34.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I got a mail saying to let you know \Nhe'd be coming back today.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.09,0:11:37.46,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He said he's looking forward \Nto seeing you at the scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.78,0:11:40.47,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, you don't mean {\i1}him{\i0}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.00,0:11:43.97,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Are we really going there, Young Master?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.40,0:11:46.72,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not only Kid who's showing up tonight,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.72,0:11:51.93,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,but I hear some scoundrel with a \Ndreadful name is also connected.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.93,0:11:53.48,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you know this, Baaya?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.94,0:11:57.24,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The symbol of a nightmare is a black horse.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.24,0:11:59.44,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I knew that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.77,0:12:02.76,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,In chess, the black horse is \Na knight that moves second.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.31,0:12:06.77,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,So if the starting white knight \Ndoesn't stand on the board,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.77,0:12:08.45,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,the game can't begin.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.08,0:12:11.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean me, Hakuba Saguru.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.45,0:12:16.94,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Between the front, back, \Nin the main building,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.94,0:12:19.50,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,and on the roof, there are \N472 riot police officers.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.50,0:12:22.76,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,On top of that, there are six \Nhelicopters watching from above.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.76,0:12:24.76,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.52,0:12:28.24,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But where'd you get that information?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.24,0:12:29.79,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Surveillance cameras.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.79,0:12:31.55,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I intercepted footage from the cameras
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.55,0:12:35.52,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,in the art museum,\N and was just going over it now.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.90,0:12:42.03,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. You could say I possess the power to \Nsee all the information the police have.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.11,0:12:44.53,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Normally,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.05,0:12:49.09,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I guide my partner through the \Nescape route I've pre-selected,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.09,0:12:50.79,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,but perhaps you don't need that.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.79,0:12:56.54,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. While I do the stealing, \Nyou can pile up the pillows and take a nap,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.54,0:12:58.67,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Nightmare-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.80,0:13:02.43,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector! Director Kondo is back!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.43,0:13:04.30,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Good grief. You're late, Director.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.70,0:13:06.30,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,My apologies.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.30,0:13:08.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,So how are things going?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.05,0:13:11.81,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We were just about to place \NDark Knight into that case.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.50,0:13:13.66,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a moment!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.94,0:13:19.29,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Just in case, I want to \Ncheck this one last time.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.33,0:13:24.32,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like there's no problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.82,0:13:28.17,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Now I just put the lid back on,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.17,0:13:31.08,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,and then we attach the high-voltage \Nelectrified chains.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.08,0:13:33.58,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Whoops! I bumped it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.03,0:13:35.23,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe it's my age.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.23,0:13:36.58,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Sheesh...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.58,0:13:39.50,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,All right! After you attach \Nthe chains, hang it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.01,0:13:42.09,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's all set.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.67,0:13:47.34,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, if I can just keep \NHakaba out of the way...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.59,0:13:52.10,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Baaya, why are we taking this street?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.10,0:13:57.70,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Just before, Inspector Nakamori told me this \Nstreet was the fastest way to get there.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.70,0:14:00.25,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Baaya, that was Kid the Phantom Thief.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.11,0:14:06.11,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He used the inspector's voice to lead us \Nto a busy street in order to slow me down.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.96,0:14:09.08,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I was such a fool!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.08,0:14:13.41,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's okay. He knew the situation wouldn't \Nbe good if I arrived before the crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.12,0:14:15.41,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Young Master!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.41,0:14:16.87,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll run the rest of the way!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.34,0:14:20.69,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello, Nakamori here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.69,0:14:22.38,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector Nakamori, it's Hakaba Saguru.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.38,0:14:23.94,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hakaba-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.94,0:14:25.88,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector, please tell me \Nwhat the situation is there.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.88,0:14:29.23,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Situation? Nothing has happened yet...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.84,0:14:32.64,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't this room a little too dark?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.64,0:14:35.49,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I just adjusted it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.49,0:14:38.91,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Opals contain around 6-10% water,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.91,0:14:43.15,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,and if they dry out, cracks form, \Nso you have to avoid bright lights.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.54,0:14:45.28,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But like this...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.76,0:14:48.15,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Certainly, when it's dark like this,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.51,0:14:51.66,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,you're practically begging \Nfor the opals to be stolen.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.82,0:14:54.40,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector, the lights!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.40,0:14:57.46,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Calm down! Switch to reserve power!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.36,0:15:06.21,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Th-The jewels are gone?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.21,0:15:08.17,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,H-How can it be?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.17,0:15:10.47,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's fine. I'm sure they're still inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.91,0:15:14.72,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Look. They've slid down the pedestal \Nand are floating on the water...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.72,0:15:16.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,They're floating?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.85,0:15:18.24,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.24,0:15:21.21,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,An opal's specific gravity \Nis between 2.10 and 2.13.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.21,0:15:23.36,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no way they could be\N floating in the water.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.36,0:15:25.21,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you telling me they're fakes?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.21,0:15:28.61,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,A-Anyway, I'll examine them, so let's \Nremove the chains and the lid...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.61,0:15:31.94,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait! Don't touch anything \Nuntil I get there...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.94,0:15:33.94,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.37,0:15:36.13,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Dammit!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.84,0:15:40.37,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Th-This {\i1}is{\i0} a fake!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.37,0:15:43.38,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,D-Damn you, Kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.80,0:15:47.63,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Chief Connery! We just received \Nword that Kid stole the jewels.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.05,0:15:51.40,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No problem. I know Nightmare's pattern.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.40,0:15:53.69,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,After running off, the two \Nof them will rendezvous.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.20,0:15:57.25,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone, follow my orders and act quickly!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.25,0:15:58.52,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hunt them both down!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.52,0:15:59.34,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Roger!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.88,0:16:06.56,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's Papa!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.56,0:16:08.08,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Papa was in that car!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.66,0:16:10.90,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Driver, follow that car!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.90,0:16:11.95,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,W-What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.26,0:16:15.08,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,There's something I have to tell Papa!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.08,0:16:19.89,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Someone from the home found a \Nnice doctor who'll fix my head!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.89,0:16:22.43,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,So he doesn't have to worry about me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.43,0:16:25.25,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He can concentrate on fighting the bad guys!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.25,0:16:27.90,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Please! Let me just tell him that!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.90,0:16:29.25,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Please!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.25,0:16:31.01,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no point in investigating now.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.53,0:16:34.89,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Before the theft, Kid switched \Nthe jewels with fakes,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.89,0:16:38.11,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,tilted the case when the lights were out,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.11,0:16:40.27,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,and made us look like fools
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.27,0:16:42.27,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,for protecting junk jewelry!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.27,0:16:44.44,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Still, don't you think it's strange?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.28,0:16:48.82,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Normally, with this much \Nwater inside, if you tilt it,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.82,0:16:53.15,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,it should leave grime from the center of the \Nsurface to the side where the water rose.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.15,0:16:56.54,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And yet, there's only grime \Non the edges of this case.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.54,0:16:59.91,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, the amount \Nof water was very low.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.29,0:17:02.41,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.47,0:17:04.64,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.64,0:17:06.29,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,A transparent acrylic panel.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.29,0:17:09.38,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He attached a small stopper to \Nall four of the case's corners,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.38,0:17:13.31,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,sunk an acrylic panel that would get caught \Non them, keeping the depth of the water low.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.31,0:17:18.30,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,A depth that would make the jewels look like \Nthey were floating after he tilted the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.30,0:17:22.96,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Then the fake jewels the director \Nexamined were actually real...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.96,0:17:25.94,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector! The director is \Nunconscious in the bathroom!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.94,0:17:27.42,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the director!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.42,0:17:30.11,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Kid disguised himself as the director \Nand made off with the jewels!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.11,0:17:32.44,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't let him out of the art museum!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.93,0:17:36.06,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He's probably already discarded that disguise
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.06,0:17:41.33,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,and flown off somewhere on that \Nwhite wing in the night sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.74,0:17:44.25,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Crap! Another miss.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.72,0:17:55.00,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That was brilliant, Kid the Phantom Thief.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.24,0:18:00.19,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? I thought we were splitting it 50-50.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.19,0:18:03.64,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Unfortunately, they're not \Nthe jewel I'm looking for.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.26,0:18:08.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think of the escape \Nroute I selected for you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.20,0:18:09.79,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Selected, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.79,0:18:11.79,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You had tons of choices, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.79,0:18:15.57,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Because you heard all of the Japanese \Npolice security measures directly.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.57,0:18:16.65,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.65,0:18:21.02,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that right, Jack Connery of Interpol?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.02,0:18:23.29,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Idiot. I told you already...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.29,0:18:25.70,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I learned of all the security measures
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.70,0:18:27.91,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,from tapping into cameras \Nand the police network...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.91,0:18:30.34,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If that's true, why did you \Nmake a counting error?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.34,0:18:31.42,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Counting?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.42,0:18:34.19,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Of the riot police: \N136 in front, 103 in back,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.19,0:18:38.10,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,185 in the main building, 47 on the roof, \Nfor a total of 471 officers.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.10,0:18:39.97,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You were one over.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.40,0:18:45.97,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. Because you included the \Ngirl who put on the uniform as a lark.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.97,0:18:48.69,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You didn't intercept the \Nsurveillance cameras.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.69,0:18:51.98,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You counted with your own eyes \Nright there on the scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.29,0:18:56.94,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I come across them occasionally \Nwhile traveling all over the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.94,0:18:58.90,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Stupid local cops
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.90,0:19:04.53,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,who purposely misreport their numbers to \NInterpol out of pride or burning with rivalry.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.53,0:19:08.45,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I always confirm \Nthe numbers with my own eyes,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.45,0:19:10.46,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,but it seems that backfired\N on me this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.46,0:19:11.84,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.12,0:19:12.50,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.71,0:19:17.00,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Any partners who figured out your real \Nidentity were rubbed out by you yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.00,0:19:21.22,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. But my partners are always thieves, \Na plague on their respective countries.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.61,0:19:27.13,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I give credit to the local cops, ensuring \Nthere's no mention of {\i1}my{\i0} gun being fired.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.81,0:19:29.10,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.10,0:19:33.81,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems my people blindly followed my orders\N and brought your local police here.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.81,0:19:35.61,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,To find your corpse.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.81,0:19:40.60,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You want to help your son so badly\N that you would kill for it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.61,0:19:44.57,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Your son has a complicated cranial disease.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.57,0:19:46.32,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You need money.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.32,0:19:50.54,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,When you told him "If Nightmare \Ndisappears, so will your disease,"
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.54,0:19:54.63,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,you meant you would retire as Nightmare\N once you saved up enough for the surgery.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.63,0:19:57.46,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It must be frustrating to have \Nto give up half every time.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.46,0:20:02.13,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And yet, if you kept all the treasure for yourself,\N no one would team up with you again.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.13,0:20:03.65,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You're right!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.65,0:20:07.31,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I have to continue \Ngiving nightmares to thieves!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.89,0:20:10.14,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Wearing this mask!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.14,0:20:13.39,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Papa!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.39,0:20:14.90,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,K-Kenta!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.57,0:20:23.57,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That was Papa! I heard Papa's voice!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.57,0:20:25.95,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you two doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.95,0:20:28.02,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He said he saw...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.02,0:20:29.70,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Kenta-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.30,0:20:31.96,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Let them go!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.49,0:20:35.71,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Let the jewels go and grab \Nmy arm with both hands!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.03,0:20:38.64,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't! This is Kenta's...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.64,0:20:40.21,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Kenta's surgery!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.44,0:20:48.72,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Papa!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.35,0:20:52.39,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna be like Papa!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.36,0:21:01.86,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Papa!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.68,0:21:05.11,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ken...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.30,0:21:30.76,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.76,0:21:33.40,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He fell trying to protect the jewels?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.40,0:21:36.19,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Given that he's holding Kid's glove,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.19,0:21:39.65,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,it looks like Kid was trying \Nto save him from falling.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.65,0:21:43.71,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The two of them had a falling out \Nand escaped, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.71,0:21:45.57,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Throwing the treasure aside...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.94,0:21:48.53,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No. He stole it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.22,0:21:51.03,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,For his son's sake.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.46,0:21:54.76,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's the nightmare called truth.
